node.text:
Organic architecture hidden beneath green dunes 💚 #archoskar
The 'Casa Organica' (178 m²).
Designed by Javier Senosiain (@javiersenosiaina, 1984).
Located in Naucalpan de Juárez, Mexico.
Video by Brenda Coto (@brendacoto).
Song by Lil Peep, 'Star Shopping'.
.
"Organic architecture seeks superior sense of use and a finer sense of comfort, expressed in organic simplicity." — Frank Lloyd Wright. #architectureoskar
.
The original idea of the project took its simile from a peanut shell: two wide oval spaces with lots of light, united by a space in low and narrow gloom. 'Organic House' is defined in two large spaces: one day and one night, with interior based on the elementary functions of man. The design seeks to show its uniqueness without losing the integration of the exterior green areas.
.
#organic #peanut #mexico #franklloydwright

node.text:
Pick your favourite Pool 😍 1, 2, 3, 4 or 5? #archoskar
.
"Water, taken in moderation, cannot hurt anybody." — Mark Twain. #architectureoskar
.
1: The 'House in Afife'.
Designed by Guilherme Machado Vaz (@guilhermachadovaz, 2018).
Located in Afife, Viana Do Castelo, Portugal.
Photo by Jose Campos (@josecamposphotographer).
.
2: The 'Wall House' (1100 m²).
Designed by José Guedes Cruz, César Marques & Marco Marinho (Guedes Cruz Arquitectos, @guedescruzarquitectos).
Located in Cascais, Lisbon, Portugal.
Photo by Ricardo Oliveira Alves (@ricardoliveiralves).
.
3: The 'Neuendorf House' (@neuendorfhouse).
Designed by Claudio Silvestrin & John Pawson (1987-1989).
Located in Mallorca, Spain.
Photo by Jelena (@jelena.marija).
.
4: The 'Oak Pass Residence' (492 m²).
Designed by SIMO design (@simo_design, 2019).
Located in Beverly Hills, California, USA.
Photo by Alex Zarour (@virtuallyherestudios).
.
5: The 'Splitwater'.
Designed & visualised by Andrea Bertaccini (2011) from Forlì, Italy.
.
#pickoftheday #pick #pool #marktwain

node.text:
Narrow contemporary residence. #archoskar
The 'El Nido House' (144 m²).
Designed by Taller estilo arquitectura (@tallerestiloarquitectura, 2020).
Located in Mérida, Yucatán, México.
Photos by Tamara Uribe (@tamara_uribe).
Description by Taller estilo arquitectura.
.
"The bird a nest, the spider a web, man friendship." — William Blake. #architectureoskar
.
The concept and name of the project 'El Nido' stands for nest and comes from the Latin word nidus. The term refers to the shelter that birds build with branches, straws and other elements. Just as they make their nests, the goal of this house was to achieve a refuge to be inhabited and enjoyed without major complications, creating a project of great simplicity yet of great spatial richness by using a minimal and simple palette of materials.
.
#merida #nest #yucatan #williamblake

#bath #bathtub #different #switzerland

node.text:
Mirrored desert cube. #archoskar
The 'Maraya Concert Hall' (5000 m²).
Designed by Giò Forma
(@gioforma, 2018) from Milan, Italy.
Located in the Al`Ulá region, Saudi Arabia.
Photo by André De Mello (@andredemello).
Description by Giò Forma.
.
"There are two ways of spreading light: to be the candle or the mirror that reflects it." — Edith Wharton. #architectureoskar
.
This giant mirror cube is a site specific "object- architecture", an experience that makes us reflect on the incomparable spectacle of the geological epic, the radical abstraction of the surroundings and the singular incursions of man into the landscape. The mirror cube will highlight the surroundings instead of competing with nature. Unique in its genre, this landscape itself becomes an exhibition space.
.
#mirror #desert #milan #concert

node.text:
Close nature connection 💚 #archoskar
The 'House OM1' (1335 m²).
Designed by AE Arquitectos (@ae.arquitectos, 2017).
Located in Guadalajara, Jalisco, Mexico.
Photos by Lorena Darquea Schettini (@loredarquea).
Description by AE Arquitectos.
.
"I believe in God, only I spell it Nature." — Frank Lloyd Wright. #architectureoskar
.
'House OM1' was conceived as a solution that balances two different concepts. Initially, there was a need to create a space where modern-day activities such as intimacy or leisure are sufficed. Another requirement was for the house to have an old-fashioned aesthetic where wood and stone were the main materials used.
.
#nature #contemporary #mexico #franklloydwright

node.text:
Architectural capital city. #archoskar
The 'København' ('Copenhagen').
Located in Copenhagen, Danmark.
Photos by Nicolas Cosedis (@copenhagenbycosedis).
.
"If a building becomes architecture, then it is art." — Arne Jacobsen. #architectureoskar
.
Copenhagen is recognised globally as an exemplar of best practice urban planning. Its thriving mixed use city centre is defined by striking contemporary architecture, engaging public spaces and an abundance of human activity. These design outcomes have been deliberately achieved through careful replanning in the second half of the 20th century, with notable contributions both by leading international architects and a wave of new successful Danish architects.
.
#copenhagen #københavn #danmark #capital
